<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Laura Muir's stunning form continued on Sunday as she clocked a world-leading time to win the 1500m at the ISTAF Berlin meet.</p>

<p>The Scot crossed in 3:57.40 to claim her fifth straight win over the past three weeks. She was more than two seconds clear of her British team-mate Laura Weightman, whose 4:00.09 was a personal best.</p>

<p>Muir, who has now gone under four minutes in each of her past four runs at the distance, lowered her own world lead by 0.46sec. </p>

<p>Laura Muir clocked a world-leading time to win the 1500metres at the ISTAF Berlin meet</p>

<p>Her performance in Germany means she holds the three fastest times for 1500m in the world in 2020, despite coming into the year with a calf problem, and she also ranks second for the 800m, behind training partner Jemma Reekie.</p>

<p>Britain’s Kristal Awuah was third in the women’s 100m in 11.44sec and Jazmin Sawyers was third in the long jump with 6.67m. Aimee Pratt was fourth in the women’s 3000m steeplechase.</p>

<p>The Scot crossed in 3:57.40 to claim her fifth straight victory over the past three weeks</p>
